cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a new framework for generative adversarial networks (GAN) that focuses on estimating the realness of generated samples from multiple angles. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and computer vision (cs.CV) as it involves training a model to generate realistic images. Additionally, the paper discusses the theoretical guarantees of the proposed framework, which relates to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of multiple angles to estimate realness also involves graph theory (cs.GR) and neural networks (cs.NE).
